      "writtenOn": "2020-08-03T13:39:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "`clang-tidy -fix` will add headers like `#include \u003cmemory\u003e`. It always adds them directly after the \"main\" header (the corresponding .h for your .cpp--that is, the main header for SkBmpCodec.cpp is SkBmpCodec.h). \n\nThe generated code from `clang-tidy -fix` for this file came out originally like this:\n\n  #include \"include/core/SkStream.h\"\n  #include \"include/private/SkColorData.h\"\n  #include \"src/codec/SkBmpCodec.h\"\n  \n  #include \u003cmemory\u003e\n  #include \"src/codec/SkBmpMaskCodec.h\"\n  #include \"src/codec/SkBmpRLECodec.h\"\n  #include \"src/codec/SkBmpStandardCodec.h\"\n  #include \"src/codec/SkCodecPriv.h\"\n\nWith \u003cmemory\u003e jammed randomly in the middle and breaking up our headers into two goofy blocks.\n\nMoving the \"main\" header to the top means that future runs of clang-tidy -fix will come out cleanly and not need fixup by hand.",
      "parentUuid": "35eb9b45_822e8e98",
      "revId": "a0104e04ce2efd5acf138d985695089aaa2ae59c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
